  "text": "The prolificacy of the Booroola Merino is well established [CITATION_1] and individual ewes can have up to 11 ovulations . It has been proposed that a major gene is responsible for the extremes in ovulation rate within the Booroola flock and three putative genotypes, FF (homozygous carriers of the fecundity gene), F+ (heterozygous carriers) and + + (non-carriers) have been proposed, based on maximum ovulation rates of > 5, < 5 and > 3 and < 3 respectively, assessed from repeated observations (Davis, [CITATION_2] ).",
